        "title": "Text 1",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p><u><strong>Activity 1: Use a Virtual Potentiometer to Control a Simulated Servo Motor</strong></u></p><p>Servo motors are commonly used in robots. They are useful due to their small size, low power consumption, and high accuracy. They can be found, for example, in the steering control of a toy car or at the helm of a ship or aircraft. In this activity, we will use a virtual potentiometer to control a simulated servo motor.&nbsp;</p>"
          ]
        }
